<P>
   KOREAVET (MESA, Ariz.) _ The soldier's mother was at home when
the news came. Rose tore open the envelope, her heart beating fast.
The Western Union telegram began: ``The Secretary of the Army has
asked me to express deep regret that your son Cpl. Rowley Arden A
has been missing in action in Korea since 1 Dec. 1950.'' Arden.
Missing. Arden had been captured. He eventuallycame home, and he is
one man who hasn't forgotten the ``Forgotten War.'' (Memorial Day
story) Story by DAVID CASSTEVENS. Story will move in the ``A''
category.
