<P>
   IMMIG-BIRTH-CERTIFICATES (Washington) _ After making it safely
to the United States, Hans Peter Bieri faced the problem that
millions of illegal immigrants have faced over the years. He had to
convince employers, government agencies, and others that he was
here legally. It was not long before Bieri discovered a little
secret: In some states, it is possible to adopt the identity of an
American citizen by simply walking into the right government office
and paying a few dollars for someone's birth certificate. By
Renwick McLean.
