<DOCNO> NYT20000529.0054 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-29 13:12 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8717 &Cx1f; taf-z
u v BC-NYT-WORLD-BUDGET &LR;      05-29 1190
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NYT-WORLD-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors at publications outside the United States may find the
following stories from the New York Times News Service for
 &UR; TUESDAY, May 30,  &LR; of particular interest:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in `i' news category)
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA-SUHARTO (Jakarta) _ The government has put former
President Suharto under house arrest as it tries to bring him to
trial for corruption and abuse of power. The house arrest, which
comes almost exactly two years after Suharto stepped down after 32
years, carries strong symbolism in a nation that is struggling to
convert itself to a democraacy. By Seth Mydans.
</P>
<P>
   (An early version of this story will move by 3 p.m. EDT.)
