<HEADER>
A8774 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l BC-TECH-KIDGEAR0530-COX     05-29 0209
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-KIDGEAR0530-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FBy Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ www.riddler.com _ For those who enjoy word games
and fun visual puzzles _ and we're not just talking kids here _
this sharply designed site is worthy of a bookmark. It's got word
search games, crosswords and mnemonic challenges, as well as a game
called scrambler that the site appropriately calls addictive. In
scrambler, a picture or drawing is split into 25 squares and then
jumbled. You've got four minutes to put it back together. There are
also three multiplayer games.
</P>
<P>
   kids.discovery.com/dinos/dinos.html _ Play paleontologist and
match dinosaur skeletons to drawings of dinosaurs. Learn about the
smallest fossil ever found (a 16-inch-long baby mussaurus).
Discover little-known facts about the most famous dinosaur, the
Tyrannosaurus, or T. rex. Did you know that the T. rex could
swallow 200 pounds of food in one bite? The site, operated by
Discovery.com, is beautifully illustrated and a great educational
resource for kids who want to learn more about those giant
creatures that once roamed the earth. A few adults might even
linger here as well.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
