<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Folding bike is a convenient traveling companion
 &HT;    By James Cummings
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Riding a bicycle is one of the most
energy-efficient ways to get around, but using a bike to travel is
sometimes impractical.
</P>
<P>
   Perhaps the route is too long or too steep or perhaps you don't
have a secure place to stash your bike.
</P>
<P>
   The Montague Corp.'s line of folding bicycles may help you get
around some of those obstacles. Montague says its bikes are
full-size vehicles that fold down to half their size in less than a
minute without the use of tools. The bikes fold down small enough
that they can be carried onto public transportation such as buses
and commuter trains. Montague makes a fabric bag with a shoulder
strap to make it easier to carry the bikes.
</P>
<P>
   The company also makes a rigid suitcase that can be used to pack
the bikes for the luggage compartments of airplanes.
</P>
<P>
   Some Montague bike users ride to work and then fold them for
storage under a desk for the day. They also fold small enough for
storage in a small closet.
</P>
<P>
   To fold a Montague bike, the rider loosens a quick release bolt
to remove the front wheel. Two quick-release bolts on the seat post
are then loosened, and the rear wheel swings around to fold over
the middle of the bike frame.
</P>
<P>
   The Montague CX 21-speed Comfort Bike, one of the company's
newest models, comes with either an 18- or 20-inch aluminum frame
and sells for $449.99. It weighs 30 pounds and folds to 36 inches
by 28 inches by 12 inches.
</P>
<P>
   Other models include a mountain bike, an off-road bike, an urban
bike, an electric bike and a tandem bike, all of which fold for
easy storage.
</P>
<P>
   For more information or to place an order, call (800) 736-5348.
Additional information is also available online at www.
montagueco.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
