<HEADER>
A8781 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l BC-TECH-LINK0530-COX     05-29 0353
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-LINK0530-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    PBy Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   _ www.internationalposter.com _ You know those nouveau French
posters of the cirque or the Cafe Bordeaux that seemingly every
single twentysomething has framed in their apartment? Even if you
aren't a rampaging Francophile, you can find something to your
liking at the International Poster Gallery, which includes
information and catalogs of posters, searchable by artist, style,
subject or country of origin. Find a nice affiche there.
</P>
<P>
   _ pinstruck.com _ Sure, we'd all like to put a hex on someone,
but who has the time? Pinstruck.com allows you to select a voodoo
doll based on the attributes of the person you'd like to curse and
e-mail your hex anonymously. No fuss, very little muss. Beware,
though: ``Think carefully before sending your curse. Some people
cannot take a joke. Make sure you respect this,'' the site warns.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.usda.gov/cnpp/using2.htm _ It now costs $160,140 to give a
newborn child the basic necessities of life over the next 17 years.
Find out how that number breaks down in the recent report from the
U.S. Department of Agriculture motto: ``We don't just stamp
supermarket ground beef''). The report is available online in Adobe
Acrobat format. You also can find reports from previous years at
this site.
</P>
<P>
   _ dangerousmonkey.com/dailyboink/ _ It sounds mind-bogglingly
stupid until you actually see it. The Daily Boink! is a site
featuring a new animation every day of someone or something
(usually a stick figure) getting hit on the head, usually by an
animated dot. Past victims have included the Pokemon Pikachu and
Jerry Lewis. Submit your own ``boinks'' here, too.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.ugo.com _ We like UGO, the UnderGround Online site that
has snarky video game news, features about entertainment and
animation, and basically everything a media-savvy person could
want. Updated seemingly every hour, this site is packed with funny
features and lots of entertainment and new media tidbits.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
