   &UR; NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   MASS-MUSEUM (North Adams, Mass.) _ Once one of the most down and
out of the New England milltowns, North Adams, Mass., has been
transformed into a Soho of the Berkshires. The unlikely catalyst of
this change was a gigantic museum in an abandoned factory featuring
trees growing upside down and sculptures made out of tons of
industrial debris. But before it could be born, itwas nearly hooted
out of existence as a $35 million state boondoggle.
</P>
<P>
   (This article is tentative and may be eliminated later.)
</P>
