<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FEATURE-BUDGET-ART-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Roy Greene  &LR; at
the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of
graphics or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REVISIONISM (Bela Crvka, Yugoslavia) _ As the anniversary
of NATO's victory in its 78-day war against Milosevic approaches,
revisionism, second-guessing, and opposition to the war are all the
rage. By Kevin Cullen. 1,200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TRADE-IMPACT (Undated) _ Although free trade theory says the
nation as a whole can benefit from deals such as the just-passed
China trade agreement, it's not likely to happen here, because
there will be no attempt by the winners compensate the losers. By
Scot Lehigh.
</P>
<P>
   TRADE-HISTORY (Washington) _ Free trade has been the spine of
every international conflict the United States has engaged in. A
