<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GOOD AND BAD IN VIDEO FILMS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Snow Falling on Cedars'' (DVD) _ Robert
Richardson's camera work delivers the cinematic equivalent of the
novel's lyrical style in this complicated story of alienation and
politics set against the internment of the American Japanese during
World War II. Richardson deserved the cinematography Oscar he was
nominated for.
</P>
<P>
   ``Man on the Moon'' _ The trouble with playing famous people is
that no matter how good the performance, it still fails. In this
case, Jim Carrey as Andy Kaufman tries extremely hard to capture
the essence of the crazy comic but falls short. The problem is that
we can compare the real Kaufman doing his famous bits on tapes such
as ``Andy Kaufman Plays Carnegie Hall.'' While the film is well
worth watching, it's too much of a paint-by-numbers movie in which
respect for Kaufman precludes Carrey from conveying what was at the
character's core _ anarchic disrespect.
</P>
<P>
   ``The 20th Century'' (10 volumes) (DVD) _ This extraordinary
series documents the 20th century through vintage newsreel film. Of
course, the idea of snaring the century on 10 volumes of video
means some of the events make Reader's Digest seem like Proust. But
as with, say, NBA highlight films, it is a terrific overview of the
United States' perspective of the past 100 years.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: June 6: ``Girl, Interrupted''(DVD), ``Mr.
Death: The Rise and Fall of Fred A. Leuchter Jr.'' (DVD),
``Backlash,'' ``Kiss the Sky'' (DVD), ``A Scandal in Paris,'' ``On
Our Merry Way'' (DVD), ``Andy Kaufman Plays Carnegie Hall.'' June
13: ``The Green Mile'' (DVD), ``Leila'' (DVD), ``The Emperor and
the Assassin'' (DVD), ``Desperately Seeking Susan'' (DVD),
``Bicentennial Man,'' ``Inferno,'' ``The Third Miracle'' (DVD),
``Light It Up.'' June 20: ``Sweet and Lowdown,'' ``Anna and the
King,'' ``Topsy-Turvy'' (DVD), ``Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo,''
``All I Wanna Do,'' ``Gun Shy,'' ``Liberty Heights'' (DVD). June
27: ``The Talented Mr. Ripley.'' July 11: ``All About My Mother''
(DVD), ``Jaws'' (DVD). July 18: ``What Planet Are You From?''
(DVD), ``Identification of a Woman,'' ``Angela's Ashes.'' July 25:
``Magnolia'' (DVD), ``The Beach.''
</P>
</TEXT>
