<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN _ By forcefully supporting the Republican Party's
current anti-abortion plank, Texas Gov. George W. Bush may have
avoided another bitter abortion fight at the convention. He
stressed his capitulation to the GOP's far right during a joint
appearance last week with Gen. Colin Powell, who is mentioned as a
possible secretary of state but who would like to remove the plank.
This means that moderates who had hoped for a more tolerant
position on abortion at the July convention might as well give up
now. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
