<HEADLINE>
BOND CALENDAR 
</HEADLINE>
  (Eds: The word PLUS in parentheses has been used instead of the
symbol, which is nontransmittable to many newspaper systems.) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Treasury's schedule of financings this week is confined to
Tuesday's auction of three- and six-month bills and a 52-week bill
being auctioned Tuesday. In observance of Memorial Day, there was
no trading Monday in U.S. Treasury securities or in futures on the
Chicago Board of Trade.
</P>
<P>
   By the close of the New York cash market on Friday, traders
said, the rate on the outstanding three-month bill was 5.64
percent, and the six-month bill was 6.06 percent. The rate for the
52-week bill was 5.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The following taxable and tax-exempt fixed-income issues are
scheduled for pricing this week:
</P>
<P>
   TAXABLE
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   DaimlerChrysler, $1.5 billion in a two-part global E-bond
offering, A1/A(PLUS)/---, Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Westvaco, $400 million in a two-part note offering, A3/A_/---.
Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Source: MCM CorporateWatch
</P>
<P>
   Ratings: Moody's Investors Service/Standard &AMP; Poor's/Duff &AMP;
Phelps Credit.
</P>
<P>
   TAX EXEMPT
</P>
<P>
   ONE DAY DURING THE WEEK
</P>
<P>
   Community Development Administration, Maryland Department of
Housing and Community Development, $138.2 million of debt
securities. Legg Mason Wood Walker.
</P>
<P>
   Alameda County, Calif., Transit, $50 million of debt securities.
M.R. Beal &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Cuyahoga County, Ohio, Hospital Facilities, $90 million of
revenue bonds. Cain Brothers.
</P>
<P>
   Fayette County, Ga., Public Facilities Authority, $55.9 million
of revenue bonds. The Robinson-Humphrey Co.
</P>
<P>
   Hawaii Housing, $100 million of debt securities. Merrill Lynch &AMP;
Co.
</P>
<P>
   New York City Water Authority, $330 million of debt securities.
PaineWebber Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Sacramento, Calif., Sanitation District, $401 million of debt
securities. Bear, Stearns &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Missouri Water Pollution Control Environmental Improvement and
Energy Resources Authority, $73.3 million of revenue notes for
clean water program.
</P>
<P>
   Tennessee Housing Development Authority, $100 million of debt
securities. Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
