PALESTINIANS-CAMPS -- Ahmad Kuleib, 19, second from the right, with
other Palestinian refugees Monday at Lebanon's border with Israel,
where he said he had journeyed ``to look at Palestine for the first
time in my life.'' From the newly opened border area here, the
300,000 Palestinians who have lived for half a century in squalid,
supposedly makeshift refugee camps in Lebanon can now gaze on the
hills of what they consider their homeland. (Rina Castelnuovo/The
