   (NYT9) BOSTON -- May 29, 2000 -- MICROBREWERY-2 -- At the Sunset
Grill and Tap in Boston, which offers about 60 American craft brews
from its 112 taps, beer enthusiasts still sample the occasional
seasonal Summer Wheat Ale or Octoberfest brew. But instead of
jumping on the new brand of the month, drinkers generally stick
with established products from brewers like Sam Adams and Sierra
Nevada. (Ed Quinn/The New York Times)
